# CountCard gcloud / Firebase auth

User runs **many** GCP/Firebase projects. Do **not** change their global gcloud default.

## Never do

- `gcloud config set project …` (changes global active project for all terminals)
- `gcloud auth application-default set-quota-project …` without explicit user approval (writes global ADC quota project)
- Assume ADC or `gcloud config get-value project` matches CountCard

## CountCard project identity

| Setting | Value |
|---------|--------|
| GCP / Firebase project ID | `countcard-94c5b` |
| Firebase Admin SA | `firebase-adminsdk-fbsvc@countcard-94c5b.iam.gserviceaccount.com` |
| Repo-local Firebase default | `.firebaserc` only (safe in this repo) |

Service account **key creation is blocked** by org policy — use ADC, not `FIREBASE_ADMIN_*` key files.

## Start of each CountCard session (before Admin SDK / deploy / E2E)

Ask the user to reauth in **their** terminal (browser required). Give them this checklist:

```bash
cd /Users/daddymac/Projects/Countcard
gcloud auth login
firebase login --reauth
gcloud auth application-default login
```

Then run verification (agent or user):

```bash
./scripts/verify-countcard-auth.sh
```

Do **not** proceed with `sprint27-e2e.mjs`, Firestore deploy, or API export tests until verify passes.

## Scoped commands (always pass project explicitly)

```bash
gcloud … --project=countcard-94c5b
GOOGLE_CLOUD_QUOTA_PROJECT=countcard-94c5b node scripts/verify-admin-sdk.mjs
firebase deploy --only firestore:rules   # uses .firebaserc in repo root
```

## If verify fails

- `invalid_rapt` / `Reauthentication failed` → user must rerun login commands above
- Key creation blocked → expected; stay on ADC path
- Wrong project in output → stop; user may be on a different GCP account or project
